name: Resource type
description: A type of computational resource used in bioinformatics.

name: Data
description: Information, represented in an information artefact (data record) that is 'understandable' by dedicated computational tools that can use the data as input or produce it as output.

name: Tool
description: A bioinformatics package or tool, e.g. a standalone application or web service.

name: Database
description: A digital data archive typically based around a relational model but sometimes using an object-oriented, tree or graph-based model.

name: Ontology
description: An ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations, a controlled vocabulary, structured glossary etc.

name: Directory metadata
description: A directory on disk from which files are read.

name: MeSH vocabulary
description: Controlled vocabulary from National Library of Medicine. The MeSH thesaurus is used to index articles in biomedical journals for the Medline/PubMED databases.

name: HGNC vocabulary
description: Controlled vocabulary for gene names (symbols) from HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee.

name: UMLS vocabulary
description: Compendium of controlled vocabularies for the biomedical domain (Unified Medical Language System).

name: Identifier
description: A text token, number or something else which identifies an entity, but which may not be persistent (stable) or unique (the same identifier may identify multiple things).

name: Database entry
description: An entry (retrievable via URL) from a biological database.

name: Molecular mass
description: Mass of a molecule.

name: Molecular charge
description: Net charge of a molecule.

name: Chemical formula
description: A specification of a chemical structure.

name: QSAR descriptor
description: A QSAR quantitative descriptor (name-value pair) of chemical structure.

name: Raw sequence
description: A raw molecular sequence (string of characters) which might include ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.

name: Sequence record
description: A molecular sequence and associated metadata.

name: Sequence set
description: A collection of one or typically multiple molecular sequences (which can include derived data or metadata) that do not (typically) correspond to molecular sequence database records or entries and which (typically) are derived from some analytical method.

name: Sequence mask character
description: A character used to replace (mask) other characters in a molecular sequence.

name: Sequence mask type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of sequence masking to perform.

name: DNA sense specification
description: The strand of a DNA sequence (forward or reverse).

name: Sequence length specification
description: A specification of sequence length(s).

name: Sequence metadata
description: Basic or general information concerning molecular sequences.

name: Sequence feature source
description: How the annotation of a sequence feature (for example in EMBL or Swiss-Prot) was derived.

name: Sequence search results
description: A report of sequence hits and associated data from searching a database of sequences (for example a BLAST search). This will typically include a list of scores (often with statistical evaluation) and a set of alignments for the hits.
synonyms: ["Sequence database search results","Sequence search hits","Database hits (sequence)","Sequence database hits"]

name: Sequence signature matches
description: Report on the location of matches (""hits"") between sequences, sequence profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) and other types of sequence signatures.
synonyms: ["Sequence profile alignment","Profile-profile alignment","Sequence motif matches","Sequence motif hits","Protein secondary database search results","Sequence-profile alignment","Sequence profile hits","Search results (protein secondary database)","Sequence profile matches"]

name: Sequence signature model
description: Data files used by motif or profile methods.

name: Sequence signature data
description: Data concering concerning specific or conserved pattern in molecular sequences and the classifiers used for their identification, including sequence motifs, profiles or other diagnostic element.

name: Sequence alignment (words)
description: Alignment of exact matches between subsequences (words) within two or more molecular sequences.

name: Dotplot
description: A dotplot of sequence similarities identified from word-matching or character comparison.

name: Sequence alignment
description: Alignment of multiple molecular sequences.

name: Sequence alignment parameter
description: Some simple value controlling a sequence alignment (or similar 'match') operation.

name: Sequence similarity score
description: A value representing molecular sequence similarity.

name: Sequence alignment metadata
description: Report of general information on a sequence alignment, typically include a description, sequence identifiers and alignment score.

name: Sequence alignment report
description: An informative report of molecular sequence alignment-derived data or metadata.

name: Profile-profile alignment
description: A profile-profile alignment (each profile typically representing a sequence alignment).

name: Sequence-profile alignment
description: Alignment of one or more molecular sequence(s) to one or more sequence profile(s) (each profile typically representing a sequence alignment).

name: Sequence distance matrix
description: A matrix of estimated evolutionary distance between molecular sequences, such as is suitable for phylogenetic tree calculation.

name: Phylogenetic character data
description: Basic character data from which a phylogenetic tree may be generated.

name: Phylogenetic tree
description: The raw data (not just an image) from which a phylogenetic tree is directly generated or plotted, such as topology, lengths (in time or in expected amounts of variance) and a confidence interval for each length.

name: Comparison matrix
description: Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for amino acid or nucleotide sequence comparison.

name: Protein topology
description: Predicted or actual protein topology represented as a string of protein secondary structure elements.

name: Protein features report (secondary structure)
description: Secondary structure (predicted or real) of a protein.

name: Protein features report (super-secondary)
description: Super-secondary structure of protein sequence(s).

name: Protein secondary structure alignment
description: Alignment of the (1D representations of) secondary structure of two or more proteins.

name: Secondary structure alignment metadata (protein)
description: An informative report on protein secondary structure alignment-derived data or metadata.

name: RNA secondary structure
description: An informative report of secondary structure (predicted or real) of an RNA molecule.

name: RNA secondary structure alignment
description: Alignment of the (1D representations of) secondary structure of two or more RNA molecules.

name: Secondary structure alignment metadata (RNA)
description: An informative report of RNA secondary structure alignment-derived data or metadata.

name: Structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a macromolecular tertiary (3D) structure or part of a structure.

name: Tertiary structure record
description: An entry from a molecular tertiary (3D) structure database.

name: Structure database search results
description: Results (hits) from searching a database of tertiary structure.

name: Structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Structure alignment report
description: An informative report of molecular tertiary structure alignment-derived data.

name: Structure similarity score
description: A value representing molecular structure similarity, measured from structure alignment or some other type of structure comparison.

name: Structural profile
description: Some type of structural (3D) profile or template (representing a structure or structure alignment).

name: Structural (3D) profile alignment
description: A 3D profile-3D profile alignment (each profile representing structures or a structure alignment).

name: Sequence-3D profile alignment
description: An alignment of a sequence to a 3D profile (representing structures or a structure alignment).

name: Protein sequence-structure scoring matrix
description: Matrix of values used for scoring sequence-structure compatibility.

name: Sequence-structure alignment
description: An alignment of molecular sequence to structure (from threading sequence(s) through 3D structure or representation of structure(s)).

name: Amino acid annotation
description: An informative report about a specific amino acid.

name: Peptide annotation
description: An informative report about a specific peptide.

name: Protein report
description: An informative human-readable report about one or more specific protein molecules or protein structural domains, derived from analysis of primary (sequence or structural) data.

name: Protein property
description: A report of primarily non-positional data describing intrinsic physical, chemical or other properties of a protein molecule or model.

name: Protein structural motifs and surfaces
description: 3D structural motifs in a protein.

name: Protein domain classification
description: Data concerning the classification of the sequences and/or structures of protein structural domain(s).

name: Protein features report (domains)
description: structural domains or 3D folds in a protein or polypeptide chain.

name: Protein architecture report
description: An informative report on architecture (spatial arrangement of secondary structure) of a protein structure.

name: Protein folding report
description: A report on an analysis or model of protein folding properties, folding pathways, residues or sites that are key to protein folding, nucleation or stabilisation centers etc.

name: Protein features (mutation)
description: Data on the effect of (typically point) mutation on protein folding, stability, structure and function.

name: Protein interaction raw data
description: Protein-protein interaction data from for example yeast two-hybrid analysis, protein microarrays, immunoaffinity chromatography followed by mass spectrometry, phage display etc.

name: Protein interaction data
description: Data concerning the interactions (predicted or known) within or between a protein, structural domain or part of a protein. This includes intra- and inter-residue contacts and distances, as well as interactions with other proteins and non-protein entities such as nucleic acid, metal atoms, water, ions etc.
synonyms: ["Protein interaction record","Protein-protein interaction data","Protein interaction report","Protein report (interaction)","Protein non-covalent interactions report","Atom interaction data","Residue interaction data"]

name: Protein family report
description: An informative report on a specific protein family or other classification or group of protein sequences or structures.

name: Vmax
description: The maximum initial velocity or rate of a reaction. It is the limiting velocity as substrate concentrations get very large.

name: Km
description: Km is the concentration (usually in Molar units) of substrate that leads to half-maximal velocity of an enzyme-catalysed reaction.

name: Nucleotide base annotation
description: An informative report about a specific nucleotide base.

name: Nucleic acid property
description: A report of primarily non-positional data describing intrinsic physical, chemical or other properties of a nucleic acid molecule.
synonyms: ["Nucleic acid physicochemical property","Nucleic acid structural property","Nucleic acid property (structural)","GC-content"]

name: Codon usage data
description: Data derived from analysis of codon usage (typically a codon usage table) of DNA sequences.

name: Gene report
description: A report on predicted or actual gene structure, regions which make an RNA product and features such as promoters, coding regions, splice sites etc.
synonyms: ["Gene annotation","Gene and transcript structure (report)","Gene function (report)","Gene structure (repot)","Nucleic acid features (gene and transcript structure)","Gene features report"]

name: Gene classification
description: A report on the classification of nucleic acid / gene sequences according to the functional classification of their gene products.

name: DNA variation
description: stable, naturally occuring mutations in a nucleotide sequence including alleles, naturally occurring mutations such as single base nucleotide substitutions, deletions and insertions, RFLPs and other polymorphisms.

name: Chromosome report
description: A human-readable collection of information about a specific chromosome.

name: Genotype/phenotype report
description: A human-readable collection of information about the set of genes (or allelic forms) present in an individual, organism or cell and associated with a specific physical characteristic, or a report concerning an organisms traits and phenotypes.

name: PCR experiment report
description: PCR experiments, e.g. quantitative real-time PCR.

name: Sequence trace
description: Fluorescence trace data generated by an automated DNA sequencer, which can be interprted as a molecular sequence (reads), given associated sequencing metadata such as base-call quality scores.

name: Sequence assembly
description: An assembly of fragments of a (typically genomic) DNA sequence.

name: RH scores
description: Radiation hybrid scores (RH) scores for one or more markers.

name: Genetic linkage report
description: A human-readable collection of information about the linkage of alleles.

name: Gene expression profile
description: Data quantifying the level of expression of (typically) multiple genes, derived for example from microarray experiments.

name: Microarray experiment report
description: microarray experiments including conditions, protocol, sample:data relationships etc.

name: Oligonucleotide probe data
description: Data on oligonucleotide probes (typically for use with DNA microarrays).

name: SAGE experimental data
description: Output from a serial analysis of gene expression (SAGE) experiment.

name: MPSS experimental data
description: Massively parallel signature sequencing (MPSS) data.

name: SBS experimental data
description: Sequencing by synthesis (SBS) data.

name: Sequence tag profile (with gene assignment)
description: Tag to gene assignments (tag mapping) of SAGE, MPSS and SBS data. Typically this is the sequencing-based expression profile annotated with gene identifiers.

name: Electron density map
description: X-ray crystallography data.

name: Raw NMR data
description: Nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) raw data, typically for a protein.

name: CD spectra
description: Protein secondary structure from protein coordinate or circular dichroism (CD) spectroscopic data.

name: Volume map
description: Volume map data from electron microscopy.
synonyms: ["3D volume map","EM volume map","Electron microscopy volume map"]

name: Electron microscopy model
description: Annotation on a structural 3D model (volume map) from electron microscopy.

name: 2D PAGE image
description: Two-dimensional gel electrophoresis image

name: Mass spectrum
description: Spectra from mass spectrometry.

name: Peptide mass fingerprint
description: A set of peptide masses (peptide mass fingerprint) from mass spectrometry.

name: Peptide identification
description: Protein or peptide identifications with evidence supporting the identifications, for example from comparing a peptide mass fingerprint (from mass spectrometry) to a sequence database, or  the set of typical spectra one obtains when running a protein through a mass spectrometer.

name: Pathway or network annotation
description: An informative report about a specific biological pathway or network, typically including a map (diagram) of the pathway.

name: Biological pathway map
description: A map (typically a diagram) of a biological pathway.

name: Data resource definition
description: A definition of a data resource serving one or more types of data, including metadata and links to the resource or data proper.

name: Workflow metadata
description: Basic information, annotation or documentation concerning a workflow (but not the workflow itself).

name: Mathematical model
description: A biological model represented in mathematical terms.

name: Statistical estimate score
description: A value representing estimated statistical significance of some observed data; typically sequence database hits.

name: EMBOSS database resource definition
description: Resource definition for an EMBOSS database.

name: Version information
description: Information on a version of software or data, for example name, version number and release date.

name: Database cross-mapping
description: A mapping of the accession numbers (or other database identifier) of entries between (typically) two biological or biomedical databases.

name: Data index
description: An index of data of biological relevance.

name: Data index report
description: A human-readable collection of information concerning an analysis of an index of biological data.

name: Database metadata
description: Basic information on bioinformatics database(s) or other data sources such as name, type, description, URL etc.

name: Tool metadata
description: Basic information about one or more bioinformatics applications or packages, such as name, type, description, or other documentation.

name: Job metadata
description: Textual metadata on a submitted or completed job.

name: User metadata
description: Textual metadata on a software author or end-user, for example a person or other software.

name: Small molecule report
description: A human-readable collection of information about a specific chemical compound.
synonyms: ["Small molecule annotation","Chemical structure report","Chemical compound annotation"]

name: Cell line report
description: A human-readable collection of information about a particular strain of organism cell line including plants, virus, fungi and bacteria. The data typically includes strain number, organism type, growth conditions, source and so on.

name: Scent annotation
description: An informative report about a specific scent.

name: Ontology term
description: A term (name) from an ontology.

name: Ontology concept data
description: Data concerning or derived from a concept from a biological ontology.

name: Keyword
description: Keyword(s) or phrase(s) used (typically) for text-searching purposes.

name: Citation
description: Bibliographic data that uniquely identifies a scientific article, book or other published material.

name: Article
description: A scientific text, typically a full text article from a scientific journal.

name: Text mining report
description: A human-readable collection of information resulting from text mining.

name: Entity identifier
description: An identifier of a biological entity or phenomenon.

name: Data resource identifier
description: An identifier of a data resource.

name: Identifier (by type of data)
description: An identifier that identifies a particular type of data.

name: Tool identifier
description: An identifier of a bioinformatics tool, e.g. an application or web service.

name: Discrete entity identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a discrete entity (any biological thing with a distinct, discrete physical existence).

name: Entity feature identifier
description: Name or other identifier of an entity feature (a physical part or region of a discrete biological entity, or a feature that can be mapped to such a thing).

name: Entity collection identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a collection of discrete biological entities.

name: Phenomenon identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a physical, observable biological occurrence or event.

name: Molecule identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a molecule.

name: Atom ID
description: Identifier (e.g. character symbol) of a specific atom.

name: Molecule name
description: Name of a specific molecule.

name: Molecule type
description: A label (text token) describing the type a molecule.

name: Chemical identifier
description: Unique identifier of a chemical compound.

name: Chromosome name
description: Name of a chromosome.

name: Peptide identifier
description: Identifier of a peptide chain.

name: Protein identifier
description: Identifier of a protein.

name: Compound name
description: Unique name of a chemical compound.

name: Chemical registry number
description: Unique registry number of a chemical compound.

name: Ligand identifier
description: Code word for a ligand, for example from a PDB file.

name: Drug identifier
description: Identifier of a drug.

name: Amino acid identifier
description: Identifier of an amino acid.

name: Nucleotide identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a nucleotide.

name: Monosaccharide identifier
description: Identifier of a monosaccharide.

name: Chemical name (ChEBI)
description: Unique name from Chemical Entities of Biological Interest (ChEBI) of a chemical compound.

name: Chemical name (IUPAC)
description: IUPAC recommended name of a chemical compound.

name: Chemical name (INN)
description: International Non-proprietary Name (INN or 'generic name') of a chemical compound, assigned by the World Health Organisation (WHO).

name: Chemical name (brand)
description: Brand name of a chemical compound.

name: Chemical name (synonymous)
description: Synonymous name of a chemical compound.

name: CAS number
description: CAS registry number of a chemical compound; a unique numerical identifier of chemicals in the scientific literature, as assigned by the Chemical Abstracts Service.

name: Chemical registry number (Beilstein)
description: Beilstein registry number of a chemical compound.

name: Chemical registry number (Gmelin)
description: Gmelin registry number of a chemical compound.

name: HET group name
description: 3-letter code word for a ligand (HET group) from a PDB file, for example ATP.

name: Amino acid name
description: String of one or more ASCII characters representing an amino acid.

name: Nucleotide code
description: String of one or more ASCII characters representing a nucleotide.

name: Polypeptide chain ID
description: Identifier of a polypeptide chain from a protein.
synonyms: ["PDB chain identifier","Polypeptide chain identifier","PDB strand id","Protein chain identifier","Chain identifier"]

name: Protein name
description: Name of a protein.

name: Enzyme identifier
description: Name or other identifier of an enzyme or record from a database of enzymes.

name: EC number
description: An Enzyme Commission (EC) number of an enzyme.

name: Enzyme name
description: Name of an enzyme.

name: Restriction enzyme name
description: Name of a restriction enzyme.

name: Sequence position specification
description: A specification (partial or complete) of one or more positions or regions of a molecular sequence or map.

name: Sequence feature ID
description: A unique identifier of molecular sequence feature, for example an ID of a feature that is unique within the scope of the GFF file.

name: Sequence position
description: A position of one or more points (base or residue) in a sequence, or part of such a specification.

name: Sequence range
description: Specification of range(s) of sequence positions.

name: Nucleic acid feature identifier
description: Name or other identifier of an nucleic acid feature.

name: Protein feature identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a protein feature.

name: Sequence feature key
description: The type of a sequence feature, typically a term or accession from the Sequence Ontology, for example an EMBL or Swiss-Prot sequence feature key.

name: Sequence feature qualifier
description: Typically one of the EMBL or Swiss-Prot feature qualifiers.

name: Sequence feature label
description: A name of a sequence feature, e.g. the name of a feature to be displayed to an end-user. Typically an EMBL or Swiss-Prot feature label.

name: EMBOSS Uniform Feature Object
description: The name of a sequence feature-containing entity adhering to the standard feature naming scheme used by all EMBOSS applications.

name: Codon name
description: String of one or more ASCII characters representing a codon.

name: Gene identifier
description: An identifier of a gene, such as a name/symbol or a unique identifier of a gene in a database.

name: Gene symbol
description: The short name of a gene; a single word that does not contain white space characters. It is typically derived from the gene name.

name: Gene ID (NCBI)
description: An NCBI unique identifier of a gene.
synonyms: ["Gene identifier (NCBI)","NCBI gene ID","Entrez gene ID","NCBI geneid","Gene identifier (Entrez)"]

name: Gene identifier (NCBI RefSeq)
description: An NCBI RefSeq unique identifier of a gene.

name: Gene identifier (NCBI UniGene)
description: An NCBI UniGene unique identifier of a gene.

name: Gene identifier (Entrez)
description: An Entrez unique identifier of a gene.

name: Gene ID (CGD)
description: Identifier of a gene or feature from the CGD database.

name: Gene ID (DictyBase)
description: Identifier of a gene from DictyBase.

name: Ensembl gene ID
description: Unique identifier for a gene (or other feature) from the Ensembl database.

name: Gene ID (SGD)
description: Identifier of an entry from the SGD database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB)
description: Identifier of a gene from the GeneDB database.

name: TIGR identifier
description: Identifier of an entry from the TIGR database.

name: TAIR accession (gene)
description: Identifier of an gene from the TAIR database.

name: Protein domain ID
description: Identifier of a protein structural domain.

name: SCOP domain identifier
description: Identifier of a protein domain (or other node) from the SCOP database.

name: CATH domain ID
description: Identifier of a protein domain from CATH.

name: SCOP concise classification string (sccs)
description: A SCOP concise classification string (sccs) is a compact representation of a SCOP domain classification.

name: SCOP sunid
description: Unique identifier (number) of an entry in the SCOP hierarchy, for example 33229.

name: CATH node ID
description: A code number identifying a node from the CATH database.

name: Kingdom name
description: The name of a biological kingdom (Bacteria, Archaea, or Eukaryotes).

name: Species name
description: The name of a species (typically a taxonomic group) of organism.

name: Strain name
description: The name of a strain of an organism variant, typically a plant, virus or bacterium.

name: URI
description: A string of characters that name or otherwise identify a resource on the Internet.

name: Database ID
description: An identifier of a biological or bioinformatics database.

name: Directory name
description: The name of a directory.

name: File name
description: The name (or part of a name) of a file (of any type).

name: Ontology name
description: Name of an ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations.

name: URL
description: A Uniform Resource Locator (URL).

name: URN
description: A Uniform Resource Name (URN).

name: LSID
description: A Life Science Identifier (LSID) - a unique identifier of some data.

name: Database name
description: The name of a biological or bioinformatics database.

name: Sequence database name
description: The name of a molecular sequence database.

name: Enumerated file name
description: The name of a file (of any type) with restricted possible values.

name: File name extension
description: The extension of a file name.

name: File base name
description: The base name of a file.

name: QSAR descriptor name
description: Name of a QSAR descriptor.

name: Database entry identifier
description: An identifier of an entry from a database where the same type of identifier is used for objects (data) of different semantic type.

name: Sequence identifier
description: An identifier of molecular sequence(s) or entries from a molecular sequence database.

name: Sequence set ID
description: An identifier of a set of molecular sequence(s).

name: Sequence signature identifier
description: Identifier of a sequence signature (motif or profile) for example from a database of sequence patterns.

name: Sequence alignment ID
description: Identifier of a molecular sequence alignment, for example a record from an alignment database.

name: Phylogenetic distance matrix identifier
description: Identifier of a phylogenetic distance matrix.

name: Phylogenetic tree ID
description: Identifier of a phylogenetic tree for example from a phylogenetic tree database.

name: Comparison matrix identifier
description: An identifier of a comparison matrix.

name: Structure ID
description: A unique and persistent identifier of a molecular tertiary structure, typically an entry from a structure database.

name: Structural (3D) profile ID
description: Identifier or name of a structural (3D) profile or template (representing a structure or structure alignment).

name: Structure alignment ID
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of tertiary structure alignments.

name: Amino acid index ID
description: Identifier of an index of amino acid physicochemical and biochemical property data.

name: Protein interaction ID
description: Identifier of a report of protein interactions from a protein interaction database (typically).

name: Protein family identifier
description: Identifier of a protein family.

name: Codon usage table name
description: Unique name of a codon usage table.

name: Transcription factor identifier
description: Identifier of a transcription factor (or a TF binding site).

name: Experiment annotation ID
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of microarray data.

name: Electron microscopy model ID
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of electron microscopy data.

name: Gene expression report ID
description: Accession of a report of gene expression (e.g. a gene expression profile) from a database.

name: Genotype and phenotype annotation ID
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of genotypes and phenotypes.

name: Pathway or network identifier
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of biological pathways or networks.

name: Workflow ID
description: Identifier of a biological or biomedical workflow, typically from a database of workflows.

name: Data resource definition ID
description: Identifier of a data type definition from some provider.

name: Biological model ID
description: Identifier of a mathematical model, typically an entry from a database.

name: Compound identifier
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of chemicals.

name: Ontology concept ID
description: A unique (typically numerical) identifier of a concept in an ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations.

name: Article ID
description: Unique identifier of a scientific article.

name: FlyBase ID
description: Identifier of an object from the FlyBase database.

name: WormBase name
description: Name of an object from the WormBase database, usually a human-readable name.

name: WormBase class
description: Class of an object from the WormBase database.

name: Sequence accession
description: A persistent, unique identifier of a molecular sequence database entry.

name: Sequence type
description: A label (text token) describing a type of molecular sequence.

name: EMBOSS Uniform Sequence Address
description: The name of a sequence-based entity adhering to the standard sequence naming scheme used by all EMBOSS applications.

name: Sequence accession (protein)
description: Accession number of a protein sequence database entry.

name: Sequence accession (nucleic acid)
description: Accession number of a nucleotide sequence database entry.

name: RefSeq accession
description: Accession number of a RefSeq database entry.

name: UniProt accession (extended)
description: Accession number of a UniProt (protein sequence) database entry. May contain version or isoform number.

name: PIR identifier
description: An identifier of PIR sequence database entry.

name: TREMBL accession
description: Identifier of a TREMBL sequence database entry.

name: Gramene primary identifier
description: Primary identifier of a Gramene database entry.

name: EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ ID
description: Identifier of a (nucleic acid) entry from the EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ databases.

name: Sequence cluster ID (UniGene)
description: A unique identifier of an entry (gene cluster) from the NCBI UniGene database.

name: dbEST accession
description: Identifier of a dbEST database entry.

name: dbSNP ID
description: Identifier of a dbSNP database entry.

name: EMBOSS sequence type
description: The EMBOSS type of a molecular sequence.

name: EMBOSS listfile
description: List of EMBOSS Uniform Sequence Addresses (EMBOSS listfile).

name: Sequence cluster ID
description: An identifier of a cluster of molecular sequence(s).

name: Sequence cluster ID (COG)
description: Unique identifier of an entry from the COG database.

name: Sequence motif identifier
description: Identifier of a sequence motif, for example an entry from a motif database.

name: Sequence profile ID
description: Identifier of a sequence profile.

name: ELM ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the ELMdb database of protein functional sites.

name: Prosite accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the Prosite database.

name: HMMER hidden Markov model ID
description: Unique identifier or name of a HMMER hidden Markov model.

name: JASPAR profile ID
description: Unique identifier or name of a profile from the JASPAR database.

name: Sequence alignment type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of a sequence alignment.

name: BLAST sequence alignment type
description: The type of a BLAST sequence alignment.

name: Phylogenetic tree type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of a phylogenetic tree.

name: TreeBASE study accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the TreeBASE database.

name: TreeFam accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the TreeFam database.

name: Comparison matrix type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of a comparison matrix.

name: Comparison matrix name
description: Unique name or identifier of a comparison matrix.

name: PDB ID
description: An identifier of an entry from the PDB database.

name: AAindex ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the AAindex database.

name: BIND accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the BIND database.

name: IntAct accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the IntAct database.

name: Protein family name
description: Name of a protein family.

name: InterPro entry name
description: Name of an InterPro entry, usually indicating the type of protein matches for that entry.

name: InterPro accession
description: Primary accession number of an InterPro entry.

name: InterPro secondary accession
description: Secondary accession number of an InterPro entry.

name: Gene3D ID
description: Unique identifier of an entry from the Gene3D database.

name: PIRSF ID
description: Unique identifier of an entry from the PIRSF database.

name: PRINTS code
description: The unique identifier of an entry in the PRINTS database.

name: Pfam accession number
description: Accession number of a Pfam entry.

name: SMART accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the SMART database.

name: Superfamily hidden Markov model number
description: Unique identifier (number) of a hidden Markov model from the Superfamily database.

name: TIGRFam ID
description: Accession number of an entry (family) from the TIGRFam database.

name: ProDom accession number
description: A ProDom domain family accession number.

name: TRANSFAC accession number
description: Identifier of an entry from the TRANSFAC database.

name: ArrayExpress accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the ArrayExpress database.

name: PRIDE experiment accession number
description: PRIDE experiment accession number.

name: EMDB ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the EMDB electron microscopy database.

name: GEO accession number
description: Accession number of an entry from the GEO database.

name: GermOnline ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the GermOnline database.

name: EMAGE ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the EMAGE database.

name: Disease ID
description: Accession number of an entry from a database of disease.

name: HGVbase ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the HGVbase database.

name: HIVDB identifier
description: Identifier of an entry from the HIVDB database.

name: OMIM ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the OMIM database.

name: KEGG object identifier
description: Unique identifier of an object from one of the KEGG databases (excluding the GENES division).

name: Pathway ID (reactome)
description: Identifier of an entry from the Reactome database.

name: Pathway ID (aMAZE)
description: Identifier of an entry from the aMAZE database.

name: Pathway ID (BioCyc)
description: Identifier of an pathway from the BioCyc biological pathways database.

name: Pathway ID (INOH)
description: Identifier of an entry from the INOH database.

name: Pathway ID (PATIKA)
description: Identifier of an entry from the PATIKA database.

name: Pathway ID (CPDB)
description: Identifier of an entry from the CPDB (ConsensusPathDB) biological pathways database, which is an identifier from an external database integrated into CPDB.

name: Pathway ID (Panther)
description: Identifier of a biological pathway from the Panther Pathways database.

name: MIRIAM identifier
description: Unique identifier of a MIRIAM data resource.

name: MIRIAM data type name
description: The name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.

name: MIRIAM URI
description: The URI (URL or URN) of a data entity from the MIRIAM database.

name: MIRIAM data type primary name
description: The primary name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.

name: MIRIAM data type synonymous name
description: A synonymous name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.

name: Taverna workflow ID
description: Unique identifier of a Taverna workflow.

name: Biological model name
description: Name of a biological (mathematical) model.

name: BioModel ID
description: Unique identifier of an entry from the BioModel database.

name: PubChem CID
description: Chemical structure specified in PubChem Compound Identification (CID), a non-zero integer identifier for a unique chemical structure.

name: ChemSpider ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the ChemSpider database.

name: ChEBI ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the ChEBI database.

name: BioPax concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the BioPax ontology.

name: GO concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from The Gene Ontology.

name: MeSH concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the MeSH vocabulary.

name: HGNC concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the HGNC controlled vocabulary.

name: NCBI taxonomy ID
description: A stable unique identifier for each taxon (for a species, a family, an order, or any other group in the NCBI taxonomy database.

name: Plant Ontology concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the Plant Ontology (PO).

name: UMLS concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the UMLS vocabulary.

name: FMA concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from Foundational Model of Anatomy.

name: EMAP concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the EMAP mouse ontology.

name: ChEBI concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the ChEBI ontology.

name: MGED concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the MGED ontology.

name: myGrid concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the myGrid ontology.

name: PubMed ID
description: PubMed unique identifier of an article.

name: DOI
description: Digital Object Identifier (DOI) of a published article.

name: Medline UI
description: Medline UI (unique identifier) of an article.

name: Tool name
description: The name of a computer package, application, method or function.

name: Tool name (signature)
description: The unique name of a signature (sequence classifier) method.

name: Tool name (BLAST)
description: The name of a BLAST tool.

name: Tool name (FASTA)
description: The name of a FASTA tool.

name: Tool name (EMBOSS)
description: The name of an EMBOSS application.

name: Tool name (EMBASSY package)
description: The name of an EMBASSY package.

name: QSAR descriptor (constitutional)
description: A QSAR constitutional descriptor.

name: QSAR descriptor (electronic)
description: A QSAR electronic descriptor.

name: QSAR descriptor (geometrical)
description: A QSAR geometrical descriptor.

name: QSAR descriptor (topological)
description: A QSAR topological descriptor.

name: QSAR descriptor (molecular)
description: A QSAR molecular descriptor.

name: Sequence set (protein)
description: Any collection of multiple protein sequences and associated metadata that do not (typically) correspond to common sequence database records or database entries.

name: Sequence set (nucleic acid)
description: Any collection of multiple nucleotide sequences and associated metadata that do not (typically) correspond to common sequence database records or database entries.

name: Sequence cluster
description: A set of sequences that have been clustered or otherwise classified as belonging to a group including (typically) sequence cluster information.

name: Psiblast checkpoint file
description: A file of intermediate results from a PSIBLAST search that is used for priming the search in the next PSIBLAST iteration.

name: HMMER synthetic sequences set
description: Sequences generated by HMMER package in FASTA-style format.

name: Proteolytic digest
description: A protein sequence cleaved into peptide fragments (by enzymatic or chemical cleavage) with fragment masses.

name: Restriction digest
description: Restriction digest fragments from digesting a nucleotide sequence with restriction sites using a restriction endonuclease.

name: PCR primers
description: Oligonucleotide primer(s) for PCR and DNA amplification, for example a minimal primer set.

name: vectorstrip cloning vector definition file
description: File of sequence vectors used by EMBOSS vectorstrip application, or any file in same format.

name: Primer3 internal oligo mishybridizing library
description: A library of nucleotide sequences to avoid during hybridisation events. Hybridisation of the internal oligo to sequences in this library is avoided, rather than priming from them. The file is in a restricted FASTA format.

name: Primer3 mispriming library file
description: A nucleotide sequence library of sequences to avoid during amplification (for example repetitive sequences, or possibly the sequences of genes in a gene family that should not be amplified. The file must is in a restricted FASTA format.

name: primersearch primer pairs sequence record
description: File of one or more pairs of primer sequences, as used by EMBOSS primersearch application.

name: Sequence cluster (protein)
description: A cluster of protein sequences.

name: Sequence cluster (nucleic acid)
description: A cluster of nucleotide sequences.

name: Sequence length
description: The size (length) of a sequence, subsequence or region in a sequence, or range(s) of lengths.

name: Word size
description: Size of a sequence word.

name: Window size
description: Size of a sequence window.

name: Sequence length range
description: Specification of range(s) of length of sequences.

name: Sequence information report
description: Report on basic information about a molecular sequence such as name, accession number, type (nucleic or protein), length, description etc.

name: Sequence property
description: An informative report about non-positional sequence features, typically a report on general molecular sequence properties derived from sequence analysis.

name: Sequence features
description: Annotation of positional features of molecular sequence(s), i.e. that can be mapped to position(s) in the sequence.

name: Sequence features (comparative)
description: Comparative data on sequence features such as statistics, intersections (and data on intersections), differences etc.

name: Sequence property (protein)
description: A report of general sequence properties derived from protein sequence data.

name: Sequence property (nucleic acid)
description: A report of general sequence properties derived from nucleotide sequence data.

name: Sequence complexity report
description: A report on sequence complexity, for example low-complexity or repeat regions in sequences.

name: Sequence ambiguity report
description: A report on ambiguity in molecular sequence(s).

name: Sequence composition report
description: A report (typically a table) on character or word composition / frequency of a molecular sequence(s).

name: Peptide molecular weight hits
description: A report on peptide fragments of certain molecular weight(s) in one or more protein sequences.

name: Base position variability plot
description: A plot of third base position variability in a nucleotide sequence.

name: Sequence composition table
description: A table of character or word composition / frequency of a molecular sequence.

name: Base frequencies table
description: A table of base frequencies of a nucleotide sequence.

name: Base word frequencies table
description: A table of word composition of a nucleotide sequence.

name: Amino acid frequencies table
description: A table of amino acid frequencies of a protein sequence.

name: Amino acid word frequencies table
description: A table of amino acid word composition of a protein sequence.

name: DAS sequence feature annotation
description: Annotation of a molecular sequence in DAS format.

name: Feature table
description: Annotation of positional sequence features, organised into a standard feature table.

name: Map
description: A map of (typically one) DNA sequence annotated with positional or non-positional features.

name: Nucleic acid features
description: An informative report on intrinsic positional features of a nucleotide sequence, formatted to be machine-readable.
synonyms: ["Nucleic acid feature table","Feature table (nucleic acid)","Genome features","Genomic features"]

name: Protein features
description: An informative report on intrinsic positional features of a protein sequence.

name: Genetic map
description: A map showing the relative positions of genetic markers in a nucleic acid sequence, based on estimation of non-physical distance such as recombination frequencies.

name: Sequence map
description: A map of genetic markers in a contiguous, assembled genomic sequence, with the sizes and separation of markers measured in base pairs.

name: Physical map
description: A map of DNA (linear or circular) annotated with physical features or landmarks such as restriction sites, cloned DNA fragments, genes or genetic markers, along with the physical distances between them.

name: Sequence signature map
description: Image of a sequence with matches to signatures, motifs or profiles.

name: Cytogenetic map
description: A map showing banding patterns derived from direct observation of a stained chromosome.

name: DNA transduction map
description: A gene map showing distances between loci based on relative cotransduction frequencies.

name: Gene map
description: Sequence map of a single gene annotated with genetic features such as introns, exons, untranslated regions, polyA signals, promoters, enhancers and (possibly) mutations defining alleles of a gene.

name: Plasmid map
description: Sequence map of a plasmid (circular DNA).

name: Genome map
description: Sequence map of a whole genome.

name: Restriction map
description: Image of the restriction enzyme cleavage sites (restriction sites) in a nucleic acid sequence.

name: InterPro compact match image
description: Image showing matches between protein sequence(s) and InterPro Entries.

name: InterPro detailed match image
description: Image showing detailed information on matches between protein sequence(s) and InterPro Entries.

name: InterPro architecture image
description: Image showing the architecture of InterPro domains in a protein sequence.

name: SMART protein schematic
description: SMART protein schematic in PNG format.

name: GlobPlot domain image
description: Images based on GlobPlot prediction of intrinsic disordered regions and globular domains in protein sequences.

name: Sequence motif matches
description: Report on the location of matches to profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) or other signatures in one or more sequences.

name: Sequence features (repeats)
description: Location of short repetitive subsequences (repeat sequences) in (typically nucleotide) sequences.

name: Gene and transcript structure (report)
description: A report on predicted or actual gene structure, regions which make an RNA product and features such as promoters, coding regions, splice sites etc.

name: Mobile genetic elements
description: regions of a nucleic acid sequence containing mobile genetic elements.

name: Nucleic acid features (quadruplexes)
description: A report on quadruplex-forming motifs in a nucleotide sequence.

name: Nucleosome exclusion sequences
description: Report on nucleosome formation potential or exclusion sequence(s).

name: Gene features (exonic splicing enhancer)
description: A report on exonic splicing enhancers (ESE) in an exon.

name: Nucleic acid features (microRNA)
description: A report on microRNA sequence (miRNA) or precursor, microRNA targets, miRNA binding sites in an RNA sequence etc.

name: Coding region
description: protein-coding regions including coding sequences (CDS), exons, translation initiation sites and open reading frames.

name: Gene features (SECIS element)
description: A report on selenocysteine insertion sequence (SECIS) element in a DNA sequence.

name: Transcription factor binding sites
description: transcription factor binding sites (TFBS) in a DNA sequence.

name: Protein features (sites)
description: A report on predicted or known key residue positions (sites) in a protein sequence, such as binding or functional sites.

name: Protein features report (signal peptides)
description: signal peptides or signal peptide cleavage sites in protein sequences.

name: Protein features report (cleavage sites)
description: cleavage sites (for a proteolytic enzyme or agent) in a protein sequence.

name: Protein features (post-translation modifications)
description: post-translation modifications in a protein sequence, typically describing the specific sites involved.

name: Protein features report (active sites)
description: catalytic residues (active site) of an enzyme.

name: Protein features report (binding sites)
description: ligand-binding (non-catalytic) residues of a protein, such as sites that bind metal, prosthetic groups or lipids.

name: Protein features (epitopes)
description: A report on antigenic determinant sites (epitopes) in proteins, from sequence and / or structural data.

name: Protein features report (nucleic acid binding sites)
description: RNA and DNA-binding proteins and binding sites in protein sequences.

name: MHC Class I epitopes report
description: A report on epitopes that bind to MHC class I molecules.

name: MHC Class II epitopes report
description: A report on predicted epitopes that bind to MHC class II molecules.

name: Protein features (PEST sites)
description: A report or plot of PEST sites in a protein sequence.

name: Sequence database hits scores list
description: Scores from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

name: Sequence database hits alignments list
description: Alignments from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

name: Sequence database hits evaluation data
description: A report on the evaluation of the significance of sequence similarity scores from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

name: MEME motif alphabet
description: Alphabet for the motifs (patterns) that MEME will search for.

name: MEME background frequencies file
description: MEME background frequencies file.

name: MEME motifs directive file
description: File of directives for ordering and spacing of MEME motifs.

name: Dirichlet distribution
description: Dirichlet distribution used by hidden Markov model analysis programs.

name: HMM emission and transition counts
description: Emission and transition counts of a hidden Markov model, generated once HMM has been determined, for example after residues/gaps have been assigned to match, delete and insert states.

name: Regular expression
description: Regular expression pattern.

name: Sequence motif
description: Any specific or conserved pattern (typically expressed as a regular expression) in a molecular sequence.

name: Sequence profile
description: Some type of statistical model representing a (typically multiple) sequence alignment.

name: Protein signature
description: An informative report about a specific or conserved protein sequence pattern.
synonyms: ["Protein site signature","Protein repeat signature","Protein family signature","Protein domain signature","InterPro entry","Protein region signature"]

name: Prosite nucleotide pattern
description: A nucleotide regular expression pattern from the Prosite database.

name: Prosite protein pattern
description: A protein regular expression pattern from the Prosite database.

name: Position frequency matrix
description: A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) that is a simple matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position.

name: Position weight matrix
description: A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) that is weighted matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position.

name: Information content matrix
description: A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) derived from a matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position that reflects information content at each position.

name: Hidden Markov model
description: A statistical Markov model of a system which is assumed to be a Markov process with unobserved (hidden) states.  For example, a hidden Markov model representation of a set or alignment of sequences.

name: Fingerprint
description: One or more fingerprints (sequence classifiers) as used in the PRINTS database.

name: Domainatrix signature
description: A protein signature of the type used in the EMBASSY Signature package.

name: HMMER NULL hidden Markov model
description: NULL hidden Markov model representation used by the HMMER package.

name: Protein family signature
description: A protein family signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein domain signature
description: A protein domain signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein region signature
description: A protein region signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein repeat signature
description: A protein repeat signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein site signature
description: A protein site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein conserved site signature
description: A protein conserved site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein active site signature
description: A protein active site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein binding site signature
description: A protein binding site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Protein post-translational modification signature
description: A protein post-translational modification signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.

name: Pair sequence alignment
description: Alignment of exactly two molecular sequences.

name: Sequence alignment (multiple)
description: Alignment of more than two molecular sequences.

name: Nucleic acid sequence alignment
description: Alignment of multiple nucleotide sequences.
synonyms: ["Sequence alignment (nucleic acid)","RNA sequence alignment","DNA sequence alignment"]

name: Protein sequence alignment
description: Alignment of multiple protein sequences.

name: Hybrid sequence alignment
description: Alignment of multiple molecular sequences of different types.

name: Sequence alignment (nucleic acid pair)
description: Alignment of exactly two nucleotide sequences.

name: Sequence alignment (protein pair)
description: Alignment of exactly two protein sequences.

name: Hybrid sequence alignment (pair)
description: Alignment of exactly two molecular sequences of different types.

name: Multiple nucleotide sequence alignment
description: Alignment of more than two nucleotide sequences.

name: Multiple protein sequence alignment
description: Alignment of more than two protein sequences.

name: Alignment score or penalty
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening or extending a gap in an alignment.

name: Score end gaps control
description: Whether end gaps are scored or not.

name: Aligned sequence order
description: Controls the order of sequences in an output sequence alignment.

name: Gap opening penalty
description: A penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap extension penalty
description: A penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap separation penalty
description: A penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

name: Terminal gap penalty
description: A penalty for gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

name: Match reward score
description: The score for a 'match' used in various sequence database search applications with simple scoring schemes.

name: Mismatch penalty score
description: The score (penalty) for a 'mismatch' used in various alignment and sequence database search applications with simple scoring schemes.

name: Drop off score
description: This is the threshold drop in score at which extension of word alignment is halted.

name: Gap opening penalty (integer)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap opening penalty (float)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap extension penalty (integer)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap extension penalty (float)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

name: Gap separation penalty (integer)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

name: Gap separation penalty (float)
description: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

name: Terminal gap opening penalty
description: A number defining the penalty for opening gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

name: Terminal gap extension penalty
description: A number defining the penalty for extending gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

name: Sequence identity
description: Sequence identity is the number (%) of matches (identical characters) in positions from an alignment of two molecular sequences.

name: Sequence similarity
description: Sequence similarity is the similarity (expressed as a percentage) of two molecular sequences calculated from their alignment, a scoring matrix for scoring characters substitutions and penalties for gap insertion and extension.

name: Sequence alignment metadata (quality report)
description: Data on molecular sequence alignment quality (estimated accuracy).

name: Sequence alignment report (site conservation)
description: Data on character conservation in a molecular sequence alignment.

name: Sequence alignment report (site correlation)
description: Data on correlations between sites in a molecular sequence alignment, typically to identify possible covarying positions and predict contacts or structural constraints in protein structures.

name: Sequence-profile alignment (Domainatrix signature)
description: Alignment of molecular sequences to a Domainatrix signature (representing a sequence alignment).

name: Sequence-profile alignment (HMM)
description: Alignment of molecular sequence(s) to a hidden Markov model(s).

name: Sequence-profile alignment (fingerprint)
description: Alignment of molecular sequences to a protein fingerprint from the PRINTS database.

name: Phylogenetic continuous quantitative data
description: Continuous quantitative data that may be read during phylogenetic tree calculation.

name: Phylogenetic discrete data
description: Character data with discrete states that may be read during phylogenetic tree calculation.

name: Phylogenetic character cliques
description: One or more cliques of mutually compatible characters that are generated, for example from analysis of discrete character data, and are used to generate a phylogeny.

name: Phylogenetic invariants
description: Phylogenetic invariants data for testing alternative tree topologies.

name: Phylogenetic report
description: A report of data concerning or derived from a phylogenetic tree, or from comparing two or more phylogenetic trees.

name: DNA substitution model
description: A model of DNA substitution that explains a DNA sequence alignment, derived from phylogenetic tree analysis.
synonyms: ["Phylogenetic tree report (DNA substitution model)","Substitution model","Sequence alignment report (DNA substitution model)"]

name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree shape)
description: Data about the shape of a phylogenetic tree.

name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree evaluation)
description: Data on the confidence of a phylogenetic tree.

name: Phylogenetic tree distances
description: Distances, such as Branch Score distance, between two or more phylogenetic trees.

name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree stratigraphic)
description: Molecular clock and stratigraphic (age) data derived from phylogenetic tree analysis.

name: Phylogenetic character contrasts
description: Independent contrasts for characters used in a phylogenetic tree, or covariances, regressions and correlations between characters for those contrasts.

name: Comparison matrix (integers)
description: Matrix of integer numbers for sequence comparison.

name: Comparison matrix (floats)
description: Matrix of floating point numbers for sequence comparison.

name: Comparison matrix (nucleotide)
description: Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for nucleotide comparison.

name: Comparison matrix (amino acid)
description: Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for amino acid comparison.
synonyms: ["Amino acid comparison matrix","Amino acid substitution matrix"]

name: Nucleotide comparison matrix (integers)
description: Matrix of integer numbers for nucleotide comparison.

name: Nucleotide comparison matrix (floats)
description: Matrix of floating point numbers for nucleotide comparison.

name: Amino acid comparison matrix (integers)
description: Matrix of integer numbers for amino acid comparison.

name: Amino acid comparison matrix (floats)
description: Matrix of floating point numbers for amino acid comparison.

name: Nucleic acid structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structure.

name: Protein structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure, or part of a structure, possibly in complex with other molecules.

name: Protein-ligand complex
description: The structure of a protein in complex with a ligand, typically a small molecule such as an enzyme substrate or cofactor, but possibly another macromolecule.

name: Carbohydrate structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a carbohydrate (3D) structure.

name: Small molecule structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for the (3D) structure of a small molecule, such as any common chemical compound.

name: DNA structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a DNA tertiary (3D) structure.

name: RNA structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for an RNA tertiary (3D) structure.

name: tRNA structure
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a tRNA tertiary (3D) structure, including tmRNA, snoRNAs etc.

name: Protein chain
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for the tertiary (3D) structure of a polypeptide chain.

name: Protein domain
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for the tertiary (3D) structure of a protein domain.

name: Protein structure (all atoms)
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

name: C-alpha trace
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).

name: Protein chain (all atoms)
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a polypeptide chain tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

name: Protein chain (C-alpha atoms)
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a polypeptide chain tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).

name: Protein domain (all atoms)
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein domain tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

name: Protein domain (C-alpha atoms)
description: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein domain tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).

name: Structure alignment (pair)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Structure alignment (multiple)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Protein structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of protein tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Nucleic acid structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Structure alignment (protein pair)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two protein tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Structure alignment (protein all atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

name: Structure alignment (protein C-alpha atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).

name: Pairwise protein tertiary structure alignment (all atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

name: Pairwise protein tertiary structure alignment (C-alpha atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).

name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment (all atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment (C-alpha atoms)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).

name: Structure alignment (nucleic acid pair)
description: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Multiple nucleic acid tertiary structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

name: RNA structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of RNA tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Structural transformation matrix
description: Matrix to transform (rotate/translate) 3D coordinates, typically the transformation necessary to superimpose two molecular structures.

name: DaliLite hit table
description: DaliLite hit table of protein chain tertiary structure alignment data.

name: Molecular similarity score
description: A score reflecting structural similarities of two molecules.

name: Root-mean-square deviation
description: Root-mean-square deviation (RMSD) is calculated to measure the average distance between superimposed macromolecular coordinates.

name: Tanimoto similarity score
description: A measure of the similarity between two ligand fingerprints.

name: 3D-1D scoring matrix
description: A matrix of 3D-1D scores reflecting the probability of amino acids to occur in different tertiary structural environments.

name: Amino acid index
description: A table of 20 numerical values which quantify a property (e.g. physicochemical or biochemical) of the common amino acids.

name: Amino acid index (chemical classes)
description: Chemical classification (small, aliphatic, aromatic, polar, charged etc) of amino acids.

name: Amino acid pair-wise contact potentials
description: Statistical protein contact potentials.

name: Amino acid index (molecular weight)
description: Molecular weights of amino acids.

name: Amino acid index (hydropathy)
description: Hydrophobic, hydrophilic or charge properties of amino acids.

name: Amino acid index (White-Wimley data)
description: Experimental free energy values for the water-interface and water-octanol transitions for the amino acids.

name: Amino acid index (van der Waals radii)
description: Van der Waals radii of atoms for different amino acid residues.

name: Enzyme report
description: An informative report on a specific enzyme.

name: Restriction enzyme report
description: An informative report on a specific restriction enzyme such as enzyme reference data.

name: Peptide molecular weights
description: List of molecular weight(s) of one or more proteins or peptides, for example cut by proteolytic enzymes or reagents.

name: Peptide hydrophobic moment
description: Report on the hydrophobic moment of a polypeptide sequence.

name: Protein aliphatic index
description: The aliphatic index of a protein.

name: Protein sequence hydropathy plot
description: A protein sequence with annotation on hydrophobic or hydrophilic / charged regions, hydrophobicity plot etc.

name: Protein charge plot
description: A plot of the mean charge of the amino acids within a window of specified length as the window is moved along a protein sequence.

name: Protein solubility
description: The solubility or atomic solvation energy of a protein sequence or structure.

name: Protein crystallizability
description: Data on the crystallizability of a protein sequence.

name: Protein globularity
description: Data on the stability, intrinsic disorder or globularity of a protein sequence.

name: Protein titration curve
description: The titration curve of a protein.

name: Protein isoelectric point
description: The isoelectric point of one proteins.

name: Protein pKa value
description: The pKa value of a protein.

name: Protein hydrogen exchange rate
description: The hydrogen exchange rate of a protein.

name: Protein extinction coefficient
description: The extinction coefficient of a protein.

name: Protein optical density
description: The optical density of a protein.

name: Protein subcellular localisation
description: An informative report on protein subcellular localisation (nuclear, cytoplasmic, mitochondrial, chloroplast, plastid, membrane etc) or destination (exported / extracellular proteins).

name: Peptide immunogenicity data
description: An report on allergenicity / immunogenicity of peptides and proteins.

name: MHC peptide immunogenicity report
description: A report on the immunogenicity of MHC class I or class II binding peptides.

name: Protein structure report
description: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific protein 3D structure(s) or structural domains.
synonyms: ["Protein structure report (domain)","Protein structure-derived report","Protein structural property","Protein property (structural)","Protein report (structure)"]

name: Protein structural quality report
description: Report on the quality of a protein three-dimensional model.
synonyms: ["Protein structure report (quality evaluation)","Protein structure validation report","Protein property (structural quality)","Protein report (structural quality)"]

name: Protein non-covalent interactions report
description: Data on inter-atomic or inter-residue contacts, distances and interactions in protein structure(s) or on the interactions of protein atoms or residues with non-protein groups.

name: Protein flexibility or motion report
description: Informative report on flexibility or motion of a protein structure.

name: Protein solvent accessibility
description: Data on the solvent accessible or buried surface area of a protein structure.

name: Protein surface report
description: Data on the surface properties (shape, hydropathy, electrostatic patches etc) of a protein structure.

name: Ramachandran plot
description: Phi/psi angle data or a Ramachandran plot of a protein structure.

name: Protein dipole moment
description: Data on the net charge distribution (dipole moment) of a protein structure.

name: Protein distance matrix
description: A matrix of distances between amino acid residues (for example the C-alpha atoms) in a protein structure.

name: Protein contact map
description: An amino acid residue contact map for a protein structure.

name: Protein residue 3D cluster
description: Report on clusters of contacting residues in protein structures such as a key structural residue network.

name: Protein hydrogen bonds
description: Patterns of hydrogen bonding in protein structures.

name: Protein non-canonical interactions
description: Non-canonical atomic interactions in protein structures.

name: CATH node
description: Information on a node from the CATH database.

name: SCOP node
description: Information on a node from the SCOP database.

name: EMBASSY domain classification
description: An EMBASSY domain classification file (DCF) of classification and other data for domains from SCOP or CATH, in EMBL-like format.

name: CATH class
description: Information on a protein 'class' node from the CATH database.

name: CATH architecture
description: Information on a protein 'architecture' node from the CATH database.

name: CATH topology
description: Information on a protein 'topology' node from the CATH database.

name: CATH homologous superfamily
description: Information on a protein 'homologous superfamily' node from the CATH database.

name: CATH structurally similar group
description: Information on a protein 'structurally similar group' node from the CATH database.

name: CATH functional category
description: Information on a protein 'functional category' node from the CATH database.

name: Protein fold recognition report
description: A report on known protein structural domains or folds that are recognised (identified) in protein sequence(s).

name: Protein-protein interaction report
description: protein-protein interaction(s), including interactions between protein domains.

name: Protein-ligand interaction report
description: An informative report on protein-ligand (small molecule) interaction(s).

name: Protein-nucleic acid interactions report
description: protein-DNA/RNA interaction(s).

name: Nucleic acid melting profile
description: Data on the dissociation characteristics of a double-stranded nucleic acid molecule (DNA or a DNA/RNA hybrid) during heating.
synonyms: ["Nucleic acid stability profile","Nucleic acid melting curve","Melting map"]

name: Nucleic acid enthalpy
description: Enthalpy of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

name: Nucleic acid entropy
description: Entropy of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

name: Nucleic acid melting temperature
description: Melting temperature of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

name: Nucleic acid stitch profile
description: Stitch profile of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

name: DNA base pair stacking energies data
description: DNA base pair stacking energies data.

name: DNA base pair twist angle data
description: DNA base pair twist angle data.

name: DNA base trimer roll angles data
description: DNA base trimer roll angles data.

name: Vienna RNA parameters
description: RNA parameters used by the Vienna package.

name: Vienna RNA structure constraints
description: Structure constraints used by the Vienna package.

name: Vienna RNA concentration data
description: RNA concentration data used by the Vienna package.

name: Vienna RNA calculated energy
description: RNA calculated energy data generated by the Vienna package.

name: Base pairing probability matrix dotplot
description: Dotplot of RNA base pairing probability matrix.

name: Nucleic acid folding report
description: A human-readable collection of information about RNA/DNA folding, minimum folding energies for DNA or RNA sequences, energy landscape of RNA mutants etc.
synonyms: ["Nucleic acid report (folding model)","Nucleic acid report (folding)","RNA secondary structure folding probablities","RNA secondary structure folding classification"]

name: Codon usage table
description: Table of codon usage data calculated from one or more nucleic acid sequences.

name: Genetic code
description: A genetic code for an organism.

name: Codon adaptation index
description: A simple measure of synonymous codon usage bias often used to predict gene expression levels.

name: Codon usage bias plot
description: A plot of the synonymous codon usage calculated for windows over a nucleotide sequence.

name: Nc statistic
description: The effective number of codons used in a gene sequence.  This reflects how far codon usage of a gene departs from equal usage of synonymous codons.

name: Codon usage fraction difference
description: The differences in codon usage fractions between two codon usage tables.

name: Pharmacogenomic test report
description: A human-readable collection of information about the influence of genotype on drug response.

name: Disease report
description: A human-readable collection of information about a specific disease.

name: Linkage disequilibrium (report)
description: A report on linkage disequilibrium; the non-random association of alleles or polymorphisms at two or more loci (not necessarily on the same chromosome).

name: Heat map
description: A graphical 2D tabular representation of expression data, typically derived from an omics experiment. A heat map is a table where rows and columns correspond to different features and contexts (for example, cells or samples) and the cell colour represents the level of expression of a gene that context.

name: Affymetrix probe sets library file
description: Affymetrix library file of information about which probes belong to which probe set.

name: Affymetrix probe sets information library file
