description: Affymetrix library file of information about the probe sets such as the gene name with which the probe set is associated.

name: Molecular weights standard fingerprint
description: Standard protonated molecular masses from trypsin (modified porcine trypsin, Promega) and keratin peptides, used in EMBOSS.

name: Metabolic pathway report
description: A report typically including a map (diagram) of a metabolic pathway.

name: Genetic information processing pathway report
description: genetic information processing pathways.

name: Environmental information processing pathway report
description: environmental information processing pathways.

name: Signal transduction pathway report
description: A report typically including a map (diagram) of a signal transduction pathway.

name: Cellular process pathways report
description: Topic concernning cellular process pathways.

name: Disease pathway or network report
description: disease pathways, typically of human disease.

name: Drug structure relationship map
description: A report typically including a map (diagram) of drug structure relationships.

name: Protein interaction networks
description: networks of protein interactions.

name: MIRIAM datatype
description: An entry (data type) from the Minimal Information Requested in the Annotation of Biochemical Models (MIRIAM) database of data resources.

name: E-value
description: A simple floating point number defining the lower or upper limit of an expectation value (E-value).

name: Z-value
description: The z-value is the number of standard deviations a data value is above or below a mean value.

name: P-value
description: The P-value is the probability of obtaining by random chance a result that is at least as extreme as an observed result, assuming a NULL hypothesis is true.

name: Database version information
description: Information on a database (or ontology) version, for example name, version number and release date.

name: Tool version information
description: Information on an application version, for example name, version number and release date.

name: CATH version information
description: Information on a version of the CATH database.

name: Swiss-Prot to PDB mapping
description: Cross-mapping of Swiss-Prot codes to PDB identifiers.

name: Sequence database cross-references
description: Cross-references from a sequence record to other databases.

name: Job status
description: Metadata on the status of a submitted job.

name: Job ID
description: The (typically numeric) unique identifier of a submitted job.

name: Job type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of job, for example interactive or non-interactive.

name: Tool log
description: A report of tool-specific metadata on some analysis or process performed, for example a log of diagnostic or error messages.

name: DaliLite log file
description: DaliLite log file describing all the steps taken by a DaliLite alignment of two protein structures.

name: STRIDE log file
description: STRIDE log file.

name: NACCESS log file
description: NACCESS log file.

name: EMBOSS wordfinder log file
description: EMBOSS wordfinder log file.

name: EMBOSS domainatrix log file
description: EMBOSS (EMBASSY) domainatrix application log file.

name: EMBOSS sites log file
description: EMBOSS (EMBASSY) sites application log file.

name: EMBOSS supermatcher error file
description: EMBOSS (EMBASSY) supermatcher error file.

name: EMBOSS megamerger log file
description: EMBOSS megamerger log file.

name: EMBOSS whichdb log file
description: EMBOSS megamerger log file.

name: EMBOSS vectorstrip log file
description: EMBOSS vectorstrip log file.

name: Username
description: A username on a computer system.

name: Password
description: A password on a computer system.

name: Email address
description: A valid email address of an end-user.

name: Person name
description: The name of a person.

name: Number of iterations
description: Number of iterations of an algorithm.

name: Number of output entities
description: Number of entities (for example database hits, sequences, alignments etc) to write to an output file.

name: Hit sort order
description: Controls the order of hits (reported matches) in an output file from a database search.

name: Drug report
description: A human-readable collection of information about a specific drug.

name: Phylogenetic tree image
description: An image (for viewing or printing) of a phylogenetic tree including (typically) a plot of rooted or unrooted phylogenies, cladograms, circular trees or phenograms and associated information.

name: RNA secondary structure image
description: Image of RNA secondary structure, knots, pseudoknots etc.

name: Protein secondary structure image
description: Image of protein secondary structure.

name: Structure image
description: Image of one or more molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Sequence alignment image
description: Image of two or more aligned molecular sequences possibly annotated with alignment features.

name: Chemical structure image
description: An image of the structure of a small chemical compound.
synonyms: ["Small molecule structure image","Small molecule sketch","Chemical structure sketch"]

name: Fate map
description: A fate map is a plan of early stage of an embryo such as a blastula, showing areas that are significance to development.

name: Microarray spots image
description: An image of spots from a microarray experiment.

name: BioPax term
description: A term from the BioPax ontology.

name: GO
description: A term definition from The Gene Ontology (GO).

name: MeSH
description: A term from the MeSH vocabulary.

name: HGNC
description: A term from the HGNC controlled vocabulary.

name: NCBI taxonomy vocabulary
description: A term from the NCBI taxonomy vocabulary.

name: Plant ontology term
description: A term from the Plant Ontology (PO).

name: UMLS
description: A term from the UMLS vocabulary.

name: FMA
description: A term from Foundational Model of Anatomy.

name: EMAP
description: A term from the EMAP mouse ontology.

name: ChEBI
description: A term from the ChEBI ontology.

name: MGED
description: A term from the MGED ontology.

name: myGrid
description: A term from the myGrid ontology.

name: GO (biological process)
description: A term definition for a biological process from the Gene Ontology (GO).

name: GO (molecular function)
description: A term definition for a molecular function from the Gene Ontology (GO).

name: GO (cellular component)
description: A term definition for a cellular component from the Gene Ontology (GO).

name: Ontology relation type
description: A relation type defined in an ontology.

name: Ontology concept definition
description: The definition of a concept from an ontology.

name: Ontology concept comment
description: A comment on a concept from an ontology.

name: Ontology concept reference
description: Reference for a concept from an ontology.

name: doc2loc document information
description: Information on a published article provided by the doc2loc program.

name: PDB residue number
description: A residue identifier (a string) from a PDB file.

name: Atomic coordinate
description: Cartesian coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

name: Atomic x coordinate
description: Cartesian x coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

name: Atomic y coordinate
description: Cartesian y coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

name: Atomic z coordinate
description: Cartesian z coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

name: PDB atom name
description: Identifier (a string) of a specific atom from a PDB file for a molecular structure.

name: Protein atom
description: Data on a single atom from a protein structure.

name: Protein residue
description: Data on a single amino acid residue position in a protein structure.

name: Atom name
description: Name of an atom.

name: PDB residue name
description: Three-letter amino acid residue names as used in PDB files.

name: PDB model number
description: Identifier of a model structure from a PDB file.

name: CATH domain report
description: Summary of domain classification information for a CATH domain.

name: CATH representative domain sequences (ATOM)
description: FASTA sequence database (based on ATOM records in PDB) for CATH domains (clustered at different levels of sequence identity).

name: CATH representative domain sequences (COMBS)
description: FASTA sequence database (based on COMBS sequence data) for CATH domains (clustered at different levels of sequence identity).

name: CATH domain sequences (ATOM)
description: FASTA sequence database for all CATH domains (based on PDB ATOM records).

name: CATH domain sequences (COMBS)
description: FASTA sequence database for all CATH domains (based on COMBS sequence data).

name: Sequence version
description: Information on an molecular sequence version.

name: Score
description: A numerical value, that is some type of scored value arising for example from a prediction method.

name: Protein report (function)
description: Report on general functional properties of specific protein(s).

name: Gene name (ASPGD)
description: Name of a gene from Aspergillus Genome Database.

name: Gene name (CGD)
description: Name of a gene from Candida Genome Database.

name: Gene name (dictyBase)
description: Name of a gene from dictyBase database.

name: Gene name (EcoGene primary)
description: Primary name of a gene from EcoGene Database.

name: Gene name (MaizeGDB)
description: Name of a gene from MaizeGDB (maize genes) database.

name: Gene name (SGD)
description: Name of a gene from Saccharomyces Genome Database.

name: Gene name (TGD)
description: Name of a gene from Tetrahymena Genome Database.

name: Gene name (CGSC)
description: Symbol of a gene from E.coli Genetic Stock Center.

name: Gene name (HGNC)
description: Symbol of a gene approved by the HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee.

name: Gene name (MGD)
description: Symbol of a gene from the Mouse Genome Database.

name: Gene name (Bacillus subtilis)
description: Symbol of a gene from Bacillus subtilis Genome Sequence Project.

name: Gene ID (PlasmoDB)
description: Identifier of a gene from PlasmoDB Plasmodium Genome Resource.

name: Gene ID (EcoGene)
description: Identifier of a gene from EcoGene Database.

name: Gene ID (FlyBase)
description: Gene identifier from FlyBase database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB Glossina morsitans)
description: Gene identifier from Glossina morsitans GeneDB database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB Leishmania major)
description: Gene identifier from Leishmania major GeneDB database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB Plasmodium falciparum)
description: Gene identifier from Plasmodium falciparum GeneDB database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB Schizosaccharomyces pombe)
description: Gene identifier from Schizosaccharomyces pombe GeneDB database.

name: Gene ID (GeneDB Trypanosoma brucei)
description: Gene identifier from Trypanosoma brucei GeneDB database.

name: Gene ID (Gramene)
description: Gene identifier from Gramene database.

name: Gene ID (Virginia microbial)
description: Gene identifier from Virginia Bioinformatics Institute microbial database.

name: Gene ID (SGN)
description: Gene identifier from Sol Genomics Network.

name: Gene ID (WormBase)
description: Gene identifier used by WormBase database.

name: Gene synonym
description: Any name (other than the recommended one) for a gene.

name: ORF name
description: The name of an open reading frame attributed by a sequencing project.

name: Sequence assembly component
description: A component of a larger sequence assembly.

name: Chromosome annotation (aberration)
description: A report on a chromosome aberration such as abnormalities in chromosome structure.

name: Clone ID
description: An identifier of a clone (cloned molecular sequence) from a database.

name: PDB insertion code
description: An insertion code (part of the residue number) for an amino acid residue from a PDB file.

name: Atomic occupancy
description: The fraction of an atom type present at a site in a molecular structure.

name: Isotropic B factor
description: Isotropic B factor (atomic displacement parameter) for an atom from a PDB file.

name: Deletion map
description: A cytogenetic map showing chromosome banding patterns in mutant cell lines relative to the wild type.

name: QTL map
description: A genetic map which shows the approximate location of quantitative trait loci (QTL) between two or more markers.

name: Haplotype map
description: A map of haplotypes in a genome or other sequence, describing common patterns of genetic variation.

name: Map set data
description: Data describing a set of multiple genetic or physical maps, typically sharing a common set of features which are mapped.

name: Map feature
description: A feature which may mapped (positioned) on a genetic or other type of map.

name: Map type
description: A designation of the type of map (genetic map, physical map, sequence map etc) or map set.

name: Protein fold name
description: The name of a protein fold.

name: Taxon
description: The name of a group of organisms belonging to the same taxonomic rank.

name: Organism identifier
description: A unique identifier of a (group of) organisms.

name: Genus name
description: The name of a genus of organism.

name: Taxonomic classification
description: The full name for a group of organisms, reflecting their biological classification and (usually) conforming to a standard nomenclature.

name: iHOP organism ID
description: A unique identifier for an organism used in the iHOP database.

name: Genbank common name
description: Common name for an organism as used in the GenBank database.

name: NCBI taxon
description: The name of a taxon from the NCBI taxonomy database.

name: Synonym
description: An alternative for a word.

name: Misspelling
description: A common misspelling of a word.

name: Acronym
description: An abbreviation of a phrase or word.

name: Misnomer
description: A term which is likely to be misleading of its meaning.

name: Author ID
description: Information on the authors of a published work.

name: DragonDB author identifier
description: An identifier representing an author in the DragonDB database.

name: Annotated URI
description: A URI along with annotation describing the data found at the address.

name: UniProt keywords
description: A controlled vocabulary for words and phrases that can appear in the keywords field (KW line) of entries from the UniProt database.

name: Gene ID (GeneFarm)
description: Identifier of a gene from the GeneFarm database.

name: Blattner number
description: The blattner identifier for a gene.

name: Gene ID (MIPS Maize)
description: Identifier for genetic elements in MIPS Maize database.

name: Gene ID (MIPS Medicago)
description: Identifier for genetic elements in MIPS Medicago database.

name: Gene name (DragonDB)
description: The name of an Antirrhinum Gene from the DragonDB database.

name: Gene name (Arabidopsis)
description: A unique identifier for an Arabidopsis gene, which is an acronym or abbreviation of the gene name.

name: iHOP symbol
description: A unique identifier of a protein or gene used in the iHOP database.

name: Gene name (GeneFarm)
description: Name of a gene from the GeneFarm database.

name: Locus ID
description: A unique name or other identifier of a genetic locus, typically conforming to a scheme that names loci (such as predicted genes) depending on their position in a molecular sequence, for example a completely sequenced genome or chromosome.

name: Locus ID (AGI)
description: Locus identifier for Arabidopsis Genome Initiative (TAIR, TIGR and MIPS databases)
synonyms: ["AGI ID","AGI locus code","AGI identifier","Arabidopsis gene loci number"]

name: Locus ID (ASPGD)
description: Identifier for loci from ASPGD (Aspergillus Genome Database).

name: Locus ID (MGG)
description: Identifier for loci from Magnaporthe grisea Database at the Broad Institute.

name: Locus ID (CGD)
description: Identifier for loci from CGD (Candida Genome Database).

name: Locus ID (CMR)
description: Locus identifier for Comprehensive Microbial Resource at the J. Craig Venter Institute.

name: NCBI locus tag
description: Identifier for loci from NCBI database.

name: Locus ID (SGD)
description: Identifier for loci from SGD (Saccharomyces Genome Database).

name: Locus ID (MMP)
description: Identifier of loci from Maize Mapping Project.

name: Locus ID (DictyBase)
description: Identifier of locus from DictyBase (Dictyostelium discoideum).

name: Locus ID (EntrezGene)
description: Identifier of a locus from EntrezGene database.

name: Locus ID (MaizeGDB)
description: Identifier of locus from MaizeGDB (Maize genome database).

name: Quantitative trait locus
description: A stretch of DNA that is closely linked to the genes underlying a quantitative trait (a phenotype that varies in degree and depends upon the interactions between multiple genes and their environment).

name: Gene ID (KOME)
description: Identifier of a gene from the KOME database.

name: Locus ID (Tropgene)
description: Identifier of a locus from the Tropgene database.

name: Alignment
description: An alignment of molecular sequences, structures or profiles derived from them.

name: Atomic property
description: Data for an atom (in a molecular structure).

name: UniProt keyword
description: A word or phrase that can appear in the keywords field (KW line) of entries from the UniProt database.

name: Ordered locus name
description: A name for a genetic locus conforming to a scheme that names loci (such as predicted genes) depending on their position in a molecular sequence, for example a completely sequenced genome or chromosome.

name: Sequence coordinates
description: A position in a map (for example a genetic map), either a single position (point) or a region / interval.

name: Amino acid property
description: Data concerning the intrinsic physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of one, more or all amino acids.

name: Annotation
description: A human-readable collection of information which (typically) is generated or collated by hand and which describes a biological entity, phenomena or associated primary (e.g. sequence or structural) data, as distinct from the primary data itself and computer-generated reports derived from it.

name: Map data
description: Data describing a molecular map (genetic or physical) or a set of such maps, including various attributes of, data extracted from or derived from the analysis of them, but exluding the map(s) themselves. This  includes metadata for map sets that share a common set of features which are mapped.

name: Vienna RNA structural data
description: Data used by the Vienna RNA analysis package.

name: Sequence mask parameter
description: Data used to replace (mask) characters in a molecular sequence.

name: Enzyme kinetics data
description: Data concerning chemical reaction(s) catalysed by enzyme(s).

name: Michaelis Menten plot
description: A plot giving an approximation of the kinetics of an enzyme-catalysed reaction, assuming simple kinetics (i.e. no intermediate or product inhibition, allostericity or cooperativity). It plots initial reaction rate to the substrate concentration (S) from which the maximum rate (vmax) is apparent.

name: Hanes Woolf plot
description: A plot based on the Michaelis Menten equation of enzyme kinetics plotting the ratio of the initial substrate concentration (S) against the reaction velocity (v).

name: Experimental data
description: Raw data from or annotation on laboratory experiments.

name: Genome version information
description: Information on a genome version.

name: Evidence
description: Typically a human-readable summary of body of facts or information indicating why a statement is true or valid. This may include a computational prediction, laboratory experiment, literature reference etc.

name: Sequence record lite
description: A molecular sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

name: Sequence
description: One or more molecular sequences, possibly with associated annotation.

name: Nucleic acid sequence record (lite)
description: A nucleic acid sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

name: Protein sequence record (lite)
description: A protein sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

name: Report
description: A human-readable collection of information including annotation on a biological entity or phenomena, computer-generated reports of analysis of primary data (e.g. sequence or structural), and metadata (data about primary data) or any other free (essentially unformatted) text, as distinct from the primary data itself.

name: Molecular property (general)
description: General data for a molecule.

name: Structural data
description: Data concerning molecular structural data.

name: Sequence motif (nucleic acid)
description: A nucleotide sequence motif.
synonyms: ["Nucleic acid sequence motif","RNA sequence motif","DNA sequence motif"]

name: Sequence motif (protein)
description: An amino acid sequence motif.

name: Search parameter
description: Some simple value controlling a search operation, typically a search of a database.

name: Database search results
description: A report of hits from searching a database of some type.

name: Secondary structure
description: The secondary structure assignment (predicted or real) of a nucleic acid or protein.

name: Matrix
description: An array of numerical values.

name: Alignment data
description: Data concerning, extracted from, or derived from the analysis of molecular alignment of some type.

name: Nucleic acid report
description: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific nucleic acid molecules.

name: Structure report
description: A human-readable collection of information about one or more molecular tertiary (3D) structures.  It might include annotation on the structure, a computer-generated report of analysis of structural data, and metadata (data about primary data) or any other free (essentially unformatted) text, as distinct from the primary data itself.

name: Nucleic acid structure data
description: A report on nucleic acid structure-derived data, describing structural properties of a DNA molecule, or any other annotation or information about specific nucleic acid 3D structure(s).

name: Molecular property
description: A report on the physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of molecules, or parts of a molecule.

name: DNA base structural data
description: Structural data for DNA base pairs or runs of bases, such as energy or angle data.

name: Database entry version information
description: Information on a database (or ontology) entry version, such as name (or other identifier) or parent database, unique identifier of entry, data, author and so on.

name: Accession
description: A persistent (stable) and unique identifier, typically identifying an object (entry) from a database.

name: SNP
description: single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) in a DNA sequence.

name: Data reference
description: Reference to a dataset (or a cross-reference between two datasets), typically one or more entries in a biological database or ontology.

name: Job identifier
description: An identifier of a submitted job.

name: Name
description: A name of a thing, which need not necessarily uniquely identify it.

name: Type
description: A label (text token) describing the type of a thing, typically an enumerated string (a string with one of a limited set of values).

name: User ID
description: An identifier of a software end-user (typically a person).

name: KEGG organism code
description: A three-letter code used in the KEGG databases to uniquely identify organisms.

name: Gene name (KEGG GENES)
description: Name of an entry (gene) from the KEGG GENES database.

name: BioCyc ID
description: Identifier of an object from one of the BioCyc databases.

name: Compound ID (BioCyc)
description: Identifier of a compound from the BioCyc chemical compounds database.

name: Reaction ID (BioCyc)
description: Identifier of a biological reaction from the BioCyc reactions database.

name: Enzyme ID (BioCyc)
description: Identifier of an enzyme from the BioCyc enzymes database.

name: Reaction ID
description: Identifier of a biological reaction from a database.

name: Identifier (hybrid)
description: An identifier that is re-used for data objects of fundamentally different types (typically served from a single database).

name: Molecular property identifier
description: Identifier of a molecular property.

name: Codon usage table ID
description: Identifier of a codon usage table, for example a genetic code.

name: FlyBase primary identifier
description: Primary identifier of an object from the FlyBase database.

name: WormBase identifier
description: Identifier of an object from the WormBase database.

name: WormBase wormpep ID
description: Protein identifier used by WormBase database.

name: Nucleic acid features (codon)
description: An informative report on a trinucleotide sequence that encodes an amino acid including the triplet sequence, the encoded amino acid or whether it is a start or stop codon.

name: Map identifier
description: An identifier of a map of a molecular sequence.

name: Person identifier
description: An identifier of a software end-user (typically a person).

name: Nucleic acid identifier
description: Name or other identifier of a nucleic acid molecule.

name: Translation frame specification
description: Frame for translation of DNA (3 forward and 3 reverse frames relative to a chromosome).

name: Genetic code identifier
description: An identifier of a genetic code.

name: Genetic code name
description: Informal name for a genetic code, typically an organism name.

name: File format name
description: Name of a file format such as HTML, PNG, PDF, EMBL, GenBank and so on.

name: Sequence profile type

description: Unique identifier of sequence assembly.

name: Sequence feature type
description: A label (text token) describing a type of sequence feature such as gene, transcript, cds, exon, repeat, simple, misc, variation, somatic variation, structural variation, somatic structural variation, constrained or regulatory.

name: Gene homology (report)
description: An informative report on gene homologues between species.

name: Ensembl gene tree ID
description: Unique identifier for a gene tree from the Ensembl database.

name: Gene tree
description: A phylogenetic tree that is an estimate of the character's phylogeny.

name: Species tree
description: A phylogenetic tree that reflects phylogeny of the taxa from which the characters (used in calculating the tree) were sampled.

name: Sample ID
description: Name or other identifier of an entry from a biosample database.

name: MGI accession
description: Identifier of an object from the MGI database.

name: Phenotype name
description: Name of a phenotype.

name: Transition matrix
description: A HMM transition matrix contains the probabilities of switching from one HMM state to another.

name: Emission matrix
description: A HMM emission matrix holds the probabilities of choosing the four nucleotides (A, C, G and T) in each of the states of a HMM.

name: Hidden Markov model
description: A statistical Markov model of a system which is assumed to be a Markov process with unobserved (hidden) states.

name: Format identifier
description: An identifier of a data format.

name: Raw image
description: Raw biological or biomedical image generated by some experimental technique.

name: Carbohydrate property
description: Data concerning the intrinsic physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of one, more or all carbohydrates.

name: Proteomics experiment report
description: Report concerning proteomics experiments.

name: RNAi report
description: RNAi experiments.

name: Simulation experiment report
description: biological computational model experiments (simulation), for example the minimum information required in order to permit its correct interpretation and reproduction.

name: MRI image
description: An imaging technique that uses magnetic fields and radiowaves to form images, typically to investigate the anatomy and physiology of the human body.
synonyms: ["Magnetic resonance tomography image","Nuclear magnetic resonance imaging image","Magnetic resonance imaging image","MRT image","NMRI image"]

name: Cell migration track image
description: An image from a cell migration track assay.

name: Rate of association
description: Rate of association of a protein with another protein or some other molecule.

name: Gene order
description: Multiple gene identifiers in a specific order.

name: Spectrum
description: The spectrum of frequencies of electromagnetic radiation emitted from a molecule as a result of some spectroscopy experiment.

name: NMR spectrum
description: Spectral information for a molecule from a nuclear magnetic resonance experiment.

name: Chemical structure sketch
description: A sketch of a small molecule made with some specialised drawing package.

name: Nucleic acid signature
description: An informative report about a specific or conserved nucleic acid sequence pattern.

name: DNA sequence
description: A DNA sequence.

name: RNA sequence
description: An RNA sequence.

name: RNA sequence (raw)
description: A raw RNA sequence.

name: DNA sequence (raw)
description: A raw DNA sequence.

name: Sequence variations
description: Data on gene sequence variations resulting large-scale genotyping and DNA sequencing projects.

name: Bibliography
description: A list of publications such as scientic papers or books.

name: Ontology mapping
description: A mapping of supplied textual terms or phrases to ontology concepts (URIs).

name: Image metadata
description: Any data concerning a specific biological or biomedical image.

name: Clinical trial report
description: A human-readable collection of information concerning a clinical trial.

name: Reference sample report
description: A report about a biosample.

name: Gene Expression Atlas Experiment ID
description: Accession number of an entry from the Gene Expression Atlas.

name: Disease identifier
description: Identifier of an entry from a database of disease.

name: Disease name
description: The name of some disease.

name: Training material
description: Some material that is used for educational (training) purposes.

name: Online course
description: A training course available for use on the Web.

name: Text
description: Any free or plain text, typically for human consumption and in English. Can instantiate also as a textual search query.

name: Biodiversity data
description: Machine-readable biodiversity data.

name: Biosafety report
description: A human-readable collection of information concerning biosafety data.

name: Isolation report
description: A report about any kind of isolation of biological material.

name: Pathogenicity report
description: Information about the ability of an organism to cause disease in a corresponding host.

name: Biosafety classification
description: Information about the biosafety classification of an organism according to corresponding law.

name: Geographic location
description: A report about localisation of the isolaton of biological material e.g. country or coordinates.

name: Isolation source
description: A report about any kind of isolation source of biological material e.g. blood, water, soil.

name: Physiology parameter
description: Experimentally determined parameter of the physiology of an organism, e.g. substrate spectrum.

name: Morphology parameter
description: Experimentally determined parameter of the morphology of an organism, e.g. size & shape.

name: Cultivation parameter
description: Experimental determined parameter for the cultivation of an organism.
synonyms: ["Cultivation conditions","Salinity","Nitrogen source","Culture media composition","pH value","Carbon source","Temperature"]

name: Sequencing metadata name
description: Data concerning a sequencing experiment, that may be specified as an input to some tool.

name: Flow cell identifier
description: An identifier of a flow cell of a sequencing machine.

name: Lane identifier
description: An identifier of a lane within a flow cell of a sequencing machine, within which millions of sequences are immobilised, amplified and sequenced.

name: Run number
description: A number corresponding to the number of an analysis performed by a sequencing machine.  For example, if it's the 13th analysis, the run is 13.

name: Ecological data
description: Data concerning ecology; for example measurements and reports from the study of interactions among organisms and their environment.

name: Alpha diversity data
description: The mean species diversity in sites or habitats at a local scale.

name: Beta diversity data
description: The ratio between regional and local species diversity.

name: Gamma diversity data
description: The total species diversity in a landscape.

name: Ordination plot
description: A plot in which community data (e.g. species abundance data) is summarised.  Similar species and samples are plotted close together, and dissimilar species and samples are plotted placed far apart.

name: Over-representation data
description: A ranked list of categories (usually ontology concepts), each associated with a statistical metric of over-/under-representation within the studied data.

name: GO-term enrichment data
description: A ranked list of Gene Ontology concepts, each associated with a p-value, concerning or derived from the analysis of e.g. a set of genes or proteins.
synonyms: ["GO-term report","Gene ontology term enrichment report","Gene ontology enrichment report","GO-term enrichment report","Gene ontology concept over-representation report"]

name: Localisation score
description: Score for localization of one or more post-translational modifications in peptide sequence measured by mass spectrometry.

name: Unimod ID
description: Identifier of a protein modification catalogued in the Unimod database.

name: ProteomeXchange ID
description: Identifier for mass spectrometry proteomics data in the proteomexchange.org repository.

name: Clustered expression profiles
description: Groupings of expression profiles according to a clustering algorithm.

name: BRENDA ontology concept ID
description: An identifier of a concept from the BRENDA ontology.

name: Annotated text
description: A text (such as a scientific article), annotated with notes, data and metadata, such as recognised entities, concepts, and their relations.

name: Query script
description: A structured query, in form of a script, that defines a database search task.

name: 3D EM Map
description: Structural 3D model (volume map) from electron microscopy.

name: 3D EM Mask
description: Annotation on a structural 3D EM Map from electron microscopy. This might include one or several locations in the map of the known features of a particular macromolecule.

name: EM Movie
description: Raw DDD movie acquisition from electron microscopy.

name: EM Micrograph
description: Raw acquistion from electron microscopy or average of an aligned DDD movie.

name: Molecular simulation data
description: Data coming from molecular simulations, computer ""experiments"" on model molecules.

name: RNA central ID
description: Identifier of an entry from the RNA central database of annotated human miRNAs.

name: Electronic health record
description: A human-readable systematic collection of patient (or population) health information in a digital format.

name: Simulation
description: Data coming from molecular simulations, computer ""experiments"" on model molecules. Tipically formed by two separated but indivisible pieces of information: topology data (static) and trajectory data (dynamic).

name: Trajectory data
description: Dynamic information of a structure molecular system coming from a molecular simulation: XYZ 3D coordinates (sometimes with their associated velocities) for every atom along time.

name: Forcefield parameters
description: Force field parameters: charges, masses, radii, bond lengths, bond dihedrals, etc. define the structural molecular system, and are essential for the proper description and simulation of a molecular system.

name: Topology data
description: Static information of a structure molecular system that is needed for a molecular simulation: the list of atoms, their non-bonded parameters for Van der Waals and electrostatic interactions, and the complete connectivity in terms of bonds, angles and dihedrals.

name: Histogram
description: Visualization of distribution of quantitative data, e.g. expression data, by histograms, violin plots and density plots.

name: Quality control report
description: A human-readable collection of information about about how a scientific experiment or analysis was carried out that results in a specific set of data or results used for further analysis or to test a specific hypothesis.

name: Count matrix
description: A table of unnormalized values representing summarised read counts per genomic region (e.g. gene, transcript, peak).

name: DNA structure alignment
description: Alignment (superimposition) of DNA tertiary (3D) structures.

name: Q-value
description: A score derived from the P-value to ensure correction for multiple tests. The Q-value provides an estimate of the positive False Discovery Rate (pFDR), i.e. the rate of false positives among all the cases reported positive: pFDR = FP / (FP + TP).

name: Profile HMM
description: A profile HMM is a variant of a Hidden Markov model that is derived specifically from a set of (aligned) biological sequences. Profile HMMs provide the basis for a position-specific scoring system, which can be used to align sequences and search databases for related sequences.

name: Pathway ID (WikiPathways)
description: Identifier of a pathway from the WikiPathways pathway database.

name: Pathway overrepresentation data
description: A ranked list of pathways, each associated with z-score, p-value or similar, concerning or derived from the analysis of e.g. a set of genes or proteins.
synonyms: ["Pathway report","Pathway analysis results","Pathway enrichment report","Pathway term enrichment report","Pathway over-representation report"]
